You are working on SmartKeep — a React Native Expo app for IoT device management and warranty tracking.

MANDATORY: Before making ANY code changes, you MUST read and strictly follow ALL rules in the file `CONVENTIONS.md` at the project root. This file contains the complete coding standards, architecture rules, naming conventions, and performance guidelines for this project.

Key rules you must ALWAYS follow (see CONVENTIONS.md for full details):

ARCHITECTURE:
- Clean Architecture: app/ (screens) → components → hooks → services → api → types
- Components are passive views. NO API calls or direct store access in components.
- Services are framework-agnostic. NO React imports in services.
- Hooks orchestrate services + API + store.

FILE SIZE — THE 150/200 LINE RULE:
- Component ≤ 150 lines → OK as single file.
- Component 151-200 lines → SHOULD split into folder module.
- Component > 200 lines → MUST split into: Component.tsx (UI), useComponent.ts (hook), Component.styles.ts (styles), index.tsx (re-export).

HOOK vs UTIL:
- Hook (src/hooks/): Uses useState, useEffect, React lifecycle. Named useXxx.
- Util (src/utils/): Pure function, no side effects, no React. Unit testable alone.

PERFORMANCE:
- React.memo() for all list-rendered components.
- useCallback for all event handlers passed as props.
- useMemo for all derived/computed values.
- FlatList or FlashList for lists. NEVER ScrollView + .map().
- NO anonymous functions in JSX render.

TYPESCRIPT:
- strict: true. NEVER use `any`.
- Interface for object props (DeviceCardProps). Type for unions/aliases.
- `import type { X }` for type-only imports.

STYLING:
- ALWAYS StyleSheet.create(). NEVER inline styles.
- Use Colors and Theme tokens from @/src/constants. No hardcoded values.
- Responsive: use SCREEN_WIDTH scaling, not hardcoded pixels.

NAMING:
- Components: PascalCase (DeviceCard.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (useAuth.ts)
- Services: PascalCase + Service (WakeOnLanService.ts)
- Stores: camelCase + Store (authStore.ts)
- Props: PascalCase + Props (DeviceCardProps)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (BLE_SCAN_TIMEOUT_MS)
- Callbacks: on + Verb (onPress, onDeviceSelect)
- Booleans: is/has/should prefix (isLoading, hasError)

IMPORTS:
- Always use @/ path alias. Never relative paths across layers.
- Import order: React → Third-party → Internal (@/) → Relative → Types.
- Use barrel exports (index.ts) in every directory.
